              RELATIONSHIP TO THE GNU GPL VERSION 2

This license is derived from the GNU General Public License, version
2, published by the Free Software Foundation. It preserves all of
the freedoms guaranteed by the GPL-2.0:

    - Freedom 0: The freedom to run the program for any purpose.
    - Freedom 1: The freedom to study how the program works, and
                  change it to make it do what you wish.
    - Freedom 2: The freedom to redistribute copies so you can help
                  others.
    - Freedom 3: The freedom to distribute copies of your modified
                  versions to others.

The sole addition is Section 11 (Brand Protection Clause), which
requires that redistributed Modified Versions preserve attribution
to the W0rkTree project and do not misrepresent themselves as
independent or original products unrelated to W0rkTree.

This additional clause is narrowly scoped:
    - It does NOT restrict modification of the source code.
    - It does NOT restrict private or internal use.
    - It does NOT restrict commercial use.
    - It does NOT restrict the creation of competing products.
    - It does NOT restrict interoperability or clean-room work.
    - It ONLY requires attribution and prohibits identity theft of
      the project.

